description: >-
  Minnesota-specific employee restrictive covenant agreement centered on
  confidentiality, trade secret protection, property return, non-disparagement,
  and narrowly drafted customer and employee non-solicitation. Omits any
  employee covenant not to compete under Minn. Stat. section 181.988, subd.
  2(a), which makes covenants not to compete void and unenforceable, and
  preserves only the covenants the statute leaves outside its definition of a
  covenant not to compete under subd. 1(a) — confidentiality and trade-secret
  protection, non-disparagement, property return, and customer and employee
  non-solicitation covenants drafted to reach only customers and colleagues the
  worker actually dealt with, keyed to Employee-initiated solicitation and a
  defined Restricted Period, so they protect relationships and information
  rather than functioning as a restraint on competition. Includes Minnesota
  choice-of-law and forum language reflecting Minn. Stat. section 181.988, subd.
  3. Drafted as a starting point for licensed counsel review.
